This paper proposes a new architecture for dual-sequence modeling in natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and associative memory (AM) in the proposed architecture, which suggests that it could be relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of the proposed architecture in textual entailment and auto-encoding tasks, which could make it relevant to categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
